    {
      "id": "f2d46f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL Once admitted, students who have prior knowledge of Italian may be required to take a language proficiency test or consult with the department language program coordinator for placement in the correct language course level. Students with prior knowledge of Italian may apply for credit by a department proficiency examination. Otherwise, Italian 1, 2, 3, and 4 are required prior to transfer. https://italian.berkeley.edu/undergraduate/language-placement For more information on this major: Undergraduate Student Services Advisor Italian Studies (510) 642-4661 issaug@berkeley.edu https://italian.berkeley.edu /",
